@page "/Components"
@layout ComponentsLayout

<div class="ui large image">
  <img src="/img/semblazor-logo.jpg" />
</div>
<p style="margin-top: 30px">
  SemanticBlazor is implementation of some Semantic UI components for Blazor.
</p>

<h4>What si Semantic UI</h4>
<p>
  User Interface is the language of the web.
  <br />
  <br />
  <SemButton Color="ButtonColor.Teal" Classes="@(new[] { ButtonClass.Basic })" Href="https://semantic-ui.com" target="_blank">More about Semantic UI</SemButton>
</p>

<h4>What si Blazor</h4>
<p>
  Blazor lets you build interactive web UIs using C# instead of JavaScript. Blazor apps are composed of reusable web UI components implemented using C#, HTML, and CSS. Both client and server code is written in C#, allowing you to share code and libraries.
</p>
<p>
  Blazor is a feature of ASP.NET, the popular web development framework that extends the .NET developer platform with tools and libraries for building web apps.
  <br />
  <br />
  <SemButton Color="ButtonColor.Teal" Classes="@(new[] { ButtonClass.Basic })" Href="https://dotnet.microsoft.com/apps/aspnet/web-apps/blazor" target="_blank">More about Blazor</SemButton>
</p>

